1. Casimir-scaling prediction:
$$
P_C = \frac{C_2(A_2)}{C_2(f)}
= \frac{\frac{k(N-k)(N+1)}{2N}}{\frac{N^2-1}{2N}}
= \frac{k(N-k)(N+1)}{N^2-1}
$$
For $N=4$ and $k=2$:
$$
P_C = \frac{2(4-2)(4+1)}{4^2-1}
= \frac{2 \cdot 2 \cdot 5}{15}
= \frac{20}{15}
= \frac{4}{3}
$$

2. Sine-formula prediction:
$$
P_S = \frac{\sin(k\pi/N)}{\sin(\pi/N)}
= \frac{\sin(2\pi/4)}{\sin(\pi/4)}
= \frac{\sin(\pi/2)}{\sin(\pi/4)}
= \frac{1}{\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}}
= \sqrt{2}
$$

3. Ratio $Q = P_C/P_S$:
$$
Q = \frac{\frac{4}{3}}{\sqrt{2}}
= \frac{4}{3\sqrt{2}}
= \frac{2\sqrt{2}}{3}
$$
